    "basedIn": "St. Petersburg, FL",
    "bio": "Kenny Coil is Break Maiden’s Tampa bred creative powerhouse. Working with local and national brands from every consumer category, he continues to immerse himself in the creative field. Marc Berenguer is Break Maiden’s Head Honcho #2. He helps lead brand creation, art direction and language translation. Before taking the US by storm in 2009, Marc lived in Barcelona where he developed a love for typography and minimal design. Artist Statement “Mangroves are our coastline's first line of defense. In addition to serving as a home to an incredible diversity of wildlife, mangroves protect our coasts from strong waves caused by storms and erosion from rivers and ocean tides. Today, these coastal habitats are threatened by over development, rising sea levels, and shrimp farming. It is essential that society adapt to prevent the destruction of these ecosystems. Our artwork depicts a colorful coastal community protected by mangroves hosting a variety of wildlife including unique species like the Roseate Spoonbill, Trunk Fish, and Great Egret. If we want to continue to enjoy nature's beauty, we must return the favor and protect our mangrove forests.”- Kenny and Marc About the Mural St. Petersburg graphic designer Kenny Coil, along with business partner Marc Berenguer, will create a mural on the topic of coastal wetlands and mangroves. Coil and Berenguer are the creative powerhouses behind Break Maiden, an award-winning studio specializing in brand identity and packaging design. Both USF graduates, Kenny and Marc designed many of St. Pete’s favorite brands like MADE Coffee and Green Bench Brewery’s Webb City Cellar. Title: Rooted in the Community",
